            \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816661,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179679/661/11816661.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"620\",\n                            \"height\": \"349\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816662,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154120+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:41 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Hagen Hopkins\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Finance Minister Bill English will be joining us for a Budget day live chat.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816662,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179680/662/11816662.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"200\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816663,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179680/663/11816663.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816664,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154120+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:41 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Hagen Hopkins\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Finance Minister Bill English will be joining us for a Budget day live chat.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816664,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179680/664/11816664.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"220\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816665,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154120+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:41 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Hagen Hopkins\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Finance Minister Bill English will be joining us for a Budget day live chat.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816665,\n                            \"layout\": \"ipad section splash 956:956\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179680/665/11816665.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"956\",\n                            \"height\": \"956\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68739990,\n            \"path\": \"/entertainment/tv-radio/68739990/John-Campbell-to-leave-TV3\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/entertainment/tv-radio/68739990/John-Campbell-to-leave-TV3\",\n            \"section\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"section-home\": \"TV & Radio\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Entertainment\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-video\",\n            \"title\": \"John Campbell to leave TV3 \",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"John Campbell to leave\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161723+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"16:17 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"SHABNAM DASTGHEIB\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/entertainment/tv-radio/68739990\",\n            \"intro\": \"TV3 staff have tweeted their support and admiration for John Campbell after it was announced the host would move on from the broadcaster.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"John Campbell is quitting his TV3's current affairs show, but will still be on screen tonight.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>TV3 staff have tweeted their support and admiration for John Campbell after it was announced the host would move on from the broadcaster.</p> <p>MediaWorks announced on Thursday that&nbsp;Campbell would no longer host the show and that it will launch a new current affairs show hosted by two presenters in the 7pm timeslot on Mondays to Thursdays on TV3.</p> <p>Executive <i>Campbell Live</i> producer Pip Keane tweeted the team were still finalising their last night together.</p> <p><i>TV3 News</i> quoted group head of news Mark Jennings saying Campbell was asked to co-host the show but he had instead decided to leave the company.</p> <p>&quot;John has decided he wants to take a break from the job and we respect his decision,&quot; Jennings said.</p> <p>MediaWorks staff were told of the news on Thursday.<br /> <br /> The show thanked their supporters on Facebook.<br /> <br /> &quot;We are still finalising when our last day on air will be. Just one point of clarification, John was offered a three year contract last year but only the first year was on Campbell Live.&quot;</p> <p><br /> <b>ALSO READ:&nbsp;</b></p> <p><b>*<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/tv-radio/68742753/sadness-and-anger-as-underdog-john-campbell-bows-out\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Sadness and anger as 'underdog' John Campbell bows out<br /> </a>*<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/68747016/so-where-to-from-here-for-campbell-live-and-what-next-for-john-campbell\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">So where to from here for Campbell Live? And what next for John Campbell?</a><br /> *<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/tv-radio/67945132/The-numbers-behind-Campbell-Live\\\">The numbers behind Campbell Live<br /> </a>*<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/dominion-post/culture/television/8170752/John-Campbell-The-Jolly-Journo\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">John Campbell: The Jolly Journo</a></b></p> <p>Group chief executive Mark Weldon and Jennings said the review was thorough and assessed a wide range of options.<br /> <br /> This was the best option, they said.</p> <p>&quot;As much as anything, this was a review of the viability of current affairs at 7pm,&quot; Jennings said.<br /> <br /> &quot;We went in without any preconceived idea of the outcome, but with a clear goal to turnaround the ratings decline...We will be bringing the best of Campbell Live over to the new show, but will be looking at a wider mix of stories.&quot;</p> <p>It seemed the day started with business as usual for Campbell himself, who tweeted about a story he was working on last night.&nbsp;</p> <p>Former TVNZ news boss and media commentator Bill Ralston said while <i>Campbell Live</i> ratings had been up in recent weeks, it was the wrong audience for TV3.</p> <p>&quot;They wanted another kind of viewer that would keep watching all the reality shows that would run afterwards, and that didn't happen.&quot;</p> <p>He expected the show would be replaced with something &quot;light and frothy&quot; that could compete with Seven Sharp on TVNZ.</p> <p>&quot;I hope John puts his feet up and then comes back on another television show or radio station so we can all have the benefit of his great interviewing.&quot;</p> <p><i>Campbell Live</i> sponsor Mazda said it had not had any discussions with MediaWorks about sponsoring the replacement show.</p> <p><i>Campbell Live</i> promotes the Japanese car-maker with the tagline &quot;driven by Mazda&quot;.</p> <p>Mazda marketing services manager Maria Tsao said John Campbell's departure from TV3 was &quot;breaking news&quot; and Mazda had not had a lot of information about the programme changes so far.</p> <p>&quot;But MediaWorks will no doubt approach us,&quot; she said.</p> <p>&quot;We continue to work with MediaWorks and we are going to be engaged with ongoing business but we haven't agreed on anything, or disagreed on anything, or accepted any new contracts for new sponsorship at this stage,&quot; she said.</p> <p>Mazda did not have a company viewpoint on the axing of Campbell Live, Tsao said.</p> <p>The review was led by TV3 news and current affairs boss Mark Jennings.</p> <p><i>Campbell Live</i>&nbsp;has surged in the ratings in recent weeks as the public swung in behind the show, which often campaigns for the underdog.</p> <p>It has regularly topped the network's ratings, outrating the 6pm news bulletin on Thursday by nearly 100,000 viewers.</p> <p>MediaWorks expected the new current affairs show to launch in 6-8 weeks, and recruiting for the hosts will begin immediately, TV3 News reported.</p> <p>Senior management team were reportedly unanimous in their decision.</p><p><blockquote class=\\\"twitter-tweet\\\" lang=\\\"en\\\"><p lang=\\\"en\\\" dir=\\\"ltr\\\">So proud of my wonderful <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/CampbellLiveNZ\\\">@CampbellLiveNZ</a> team &amp; marvellous <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/JohnJCampbell\\\">@JohnJCampbell</a>. Still finalising our last night on air together. Thank you all.</p>&mdash; Pip Keane (@pipkeane) <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/pipkeane/status/601232899241717761\\\">May 21, 2015</a></blockquote> <script async src=\\\"http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\\\" charset=\\\"utf-8\\\"></script>\\n<blockquote class=\\\"twitter-tweet\\\" lang=\\\"en\\\"><p lang=\\\"en\\\" dir=\\\"ltr\\\">my hero and my friend <a href=\\\"http://t.co/ENooqvgpDS\\\">pic.twitter.com/ENooqvgpDS</a></p>&mdash; Jono Hutchison (@jonohutchison) <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/jonohutchison/status/601228223322558464\\\">May 21, 2015</a></blockquote>\\n<script async src=\\\"http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\\\" charset=\\\"utf-8\\\"></script>\\n<blockquote class=\\\"twitter-tweet\\\" lang=\\\"en\\\"><p lang=\\\"en\\\" dir=\\\"ltr\\\">When they shut down the TV3 cafe and the lady was crying and someone said &quot;I&#39;ll go get John&quot; and John Campbell showed up and hugged them.</p>&mdash; Guy Williams (@guywilliamsguy) <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/guywilliamsguy/status/601219896911929345\\\">May 21, 2015</a></blockquote>\\n<script async src=\\\"http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\\\" charset=\\\"utf-8\\\"></script>\\n\\n<blockquote class=\\\"twitter-tweet\\\" lang=\\\"en\\\"><p lang=\\\"en\\\" dir=\\\"ltr\\\">i feel exactly like i felt when my favourite intermediate teacher left. similar reasons: mentor, friend, life advice, laughs</p>&mdash; David Farrier (@davidfarrier) <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/davidfarrier/status/601220262298681345\\\">May 21, 2015</a></blockquote>\\n<script async src=\\\"http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\\\" charset=\\\"utf-8\\\"></script>\\n</p><p><div id=\\\"fb-root\\\"></div><script>(function(d, s, id) {  var js, fjs = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];  if (d.getElementById(id)) return;  js = d.createElement(s); js.id = id;  js.src = \\\"//connect.facebook.net/en_GB/sdk.js#xfbml=1&version=v2.3\\\";  fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js, fjs);}(document, 'script', 'facebook-jssdk'));</script><div class=\\\"fb-post\\\" data-href=\\\"https://www.facebook.com/CampbellLiveNZ/posts/10155670218625226\\\" data-width=\\\"500\\\"><div class=\\\"fb-xfbml-parse-ignore\\\"><blockquote cite=\\\"https://www.facebook.com/CampbellLiveNZ/posts/10155670218625226\\\"><p>Thank you all for your support over the past seven weeks. We are still finalising when our last day on air will be. Just...</p>Posted by <a href=\\\"https://www.facebook.com/CampbellLiveNZ\\\">Campbell Live</a> on <a href=\\\"https://www.facebook.com/CampbellLiveNZ/posts/10155670218625226\\\">Wednesday, 20 May 2015</a></blockquote></div></div></p><p><blockquote class=\\\"twitter-tweet\\\" lang=\\\"en\\\"><p lang=\\\"en\\\" dir=\\\"ltr\\\">Budget Day. Just home from filming a Mum of 4 ending her 19 hr day. Child care, two jobs, office cleaning until midnight. Up again at 0500.</p>&mdash; John Campbell (@JohnJCampbell) <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/JohnJCampbell/status/601001752721141760\\\">May 20, 2015</a></blockquote>\\n<script async src=\\\"http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\\\" charset=\\\"utf-8\\\"></script></p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816977,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T160425+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:04 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"caption\": \"*\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816977,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181872/977/11816977.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817139,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161752+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:17 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n                    \"caption\": \"John Campbell will leave TV3 and his show will be replaced by a four day a week news and current affairs show\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817139,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181872/139/11817139.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"59\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817140,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161752+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:17 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n                    \"caption\": \"John Campbell will leave TV3 and his show will be replaced by a four day a week news and current affairs show\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817140,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181872/140/11817140.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"238\",\n                            \"height\": \"284\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817141,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161752+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:17 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n                    \"caption\": \"John Campbell will leave TV3 and his show will be replaced by a four day a week news and current affairs show\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817141,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181872/141/11817141.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"198\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817142,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181872/142/11817142.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"59\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817143,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161753+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:17 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n                    \"caption\": \"John Campbell will leave TV3 and his show will be replaced by a four day a week news and current affairs show\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817143,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181873/143/11817143.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"218\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ],\n            \"videos\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816936,\n                    \"layout\": \"Standard Video\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"aap\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"AAP\",\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T160031+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:00 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Youtube\",\n                    \"caption\": \"John Campbell is leaving TV3, with Mediaworks replacing Campbell Live with a relaunched current affairs show four nights a week.\",\n                    \"src\": \"http://file2.stuff.co.nz/1432180831/937/11816937.mp4\",\n                    \"video_poster\": {\n                        \"id\": 11816938,\n                        \"layout\": \"Video Image\",\n                        \"src\": \"http://file2.stuff.co.nz/1432183053/938/11816938.jpg\",\n                        \"width\": \"640\",\n                        \"height\": \"360\"\n                    }\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68747242,\n            \"path\": \"/national/68747242/Historic-remains-identified-as-missing-Invercargill-man\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/national/68747242/Historic-remains-identified-as-missing-Invercargill-man\",\n            \"section\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"section-home\": \"National\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"National\",\n            \"layout\": \"a-standard\",\n            \"title\": \"Historic remains identified as missing Invercargill man\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Historic remains identified as missing Invercargill man\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T160720+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"16:07 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": null,\n            \"source_code\": \"the-southland-times\",\n            \"source_name\": \"The Southland Times\",\n            \"intro\": \"Police have confirmed human remains found on the Tasman Glacier in February belong to former Invercargill man David Moen.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"Police have confirmed human remains found on the Tasman Glacier in February belong to former Invercargill man David Moen.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>Police have confirmed human remains found on the Tasman Glacier in February belong to former Invercargill man David Moen.</p> <p>Moen, 19, was climbing with a friend 41 years ago, when they were caught in an avalanche.</p> <p>A 20-hour search recovered his friend and Moen's bag, but the young man's body was not recovered until earlier this year.</p> <p><b>READ MORE</b>:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/national/66984286/Avid-tramper-David-Moen-found-40-years-after-death\\\">'Avid tramper' David Moen found 40 years after death</a></p> <p>Canterbury police area commander Inspector Dave Gaskin said it was good to be able to return David to his family.</p> <p>&quot;We are pleased that we have been able to return David to his immediate family. He was lost in tragic circumstances doing a sport he loved. Canterbury police will continue to support David's family as they come to terms with David being returned to them over 41 years after he went missing.&quot;</p> <p>A statement from Moen's family released by police said they were glad to have David returned to them.</p> <p>&quot;We cannot put into words what it feels like to have David returned to us after all this time, but we are taken back to when he first went missing back in 1973. We are a very close family and losing David so unexpectedly was really hard on us all and his loss was felt enormously by us and his friends. David was friendly with everyone and lived life to the full.&nbsp; He had an infectious sense of humour and was always smiling.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;David shared his love of the outdoors with other members of the family. He learned to climb at school where he was a Queens Scout and continued to learn and hone his climbing skills. He was a great outdoorsman making his loss that much harder to comprehend.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;We are very grateful for the support of our family and friends, particularly while the remains were being identified and we just didn't know whether it was David or not.&nbsp; It has been a very difficult process for everyone involved and we would like to thank Canterbury police who have been extremely supportive, respectful and compassionate and this has brought us great comfort, knowing they were there for us.</p> <p>David's spirit still remains in the beautiful, peaceful environment which claimed the life of a wonderful and dearly loved young man in the prime of his life.&quot;</p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817131,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161624+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:16 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"SUPPLIED\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"the-southland-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"The Southland Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"David Moen was found on the Tasman Glacier 41 years after he went missing.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817131,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181784/131/11817131.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"58\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817132,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161624+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:16 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"SUPPLIED\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"the-southland-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"The Southland Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"David Moen was found on the Tasman Glacier 41 years after he went missing.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817132,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181784/132/11817132.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"238\",\n                            \"height\": \"286\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817133,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161624+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:16 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"SUPPLIED\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"the-southland-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"The Southland Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"David Moen was found on the Tasman Glacier 41 years after he went missing.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817133,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181784/133/11817133.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"197\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817134,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181784/134/11817134.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"59\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817135,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161624+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:16 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"SUPPLIED\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"the-southland-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"The Southland Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"David Moen was found on the Tasman Glacier 41 years after he went missing.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817135,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181784/135/11817135.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"216\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817136,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T161624+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:16 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"SUPPLIED\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"the-southland-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"The Southland Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"David Moen was found on the Tasman Glacier 41 years after he went missing.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817136,\n                            \"layout\": \"ipad section splash 956:956\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432181784/136/11817136.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"956\",\n                            \"height\": \"956\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68745803,\n            \"path\": \"/sport/opinion/68745803/Johnstone-Dean-Barker-move-to-Team-Japan-could-haunt-Kiwis\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/sport/opinion/68745803/Johnstone-Dean-Barker-move-to-Team-Japan-could-haunt-Kiwis\",\n            \"section\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"section-home\": \"Opinion\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Sport\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-image\",\n            \"title\": \"Johnstone: Dean Barker move to Team Japan could haunt Kiwis\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Barker move to Team Japan could haunt Kiwis\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154332+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"15:43 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"DUNCAN JOHNSTONE\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/sport/opinion/68745803\",\n            \"intro\": \"Suddenly the America's Cup just got interesting for New Zealanders again.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"Suddenly the America's Cup just got interesting for New Zealanders again, says Duncan Johnstone.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>Suddenly the America's Cup just got interesting for New Zealanders again.</p> <p><a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/other-sports/68741060/dean-barker-named-ceo-skipper-for-japans-americas-cup-entry\\\"><b>Dean Barker's signing by Team Japan</b></a> will ensure an added edge to a 2017 regatta that was waning from public focus with the ongoing problems at Team New Zealand and the questionable changes by America's Cup bosses over the details of the Bermuda event.</p> <p>Will Barker come back to haunt his old team? Can he make the Japanese competitive in a game of catchup? Will he raid the surplus Kiwi talent to try to help the Asian syndicate?</p> <p>Barker's departure from Team New Zealand drew a mixed response. Many agreed that after 20 years in the game and three consecutive failures he had done his time as the man at the helm. But most felt his axing from the wheel was very poorly handled.</p> <p>The classy Barker made a dignified exit on his own terms, politely refusing the coaching job that was offered as an alternative and hardly uttering a bitter word about his old bosses as he sailed off into the sunset.</p> <p>But he's come back over the horizon and will certainly have Team New Zealand in his sights in his new position that involves work on and off the water as chief executive and skipper.</p> <p>Team New Zealand are proven old hands in this murky game and will back their experience to be competitive again. They have design information that has repeatedly kept them at or near the head of the pack. But the field has evened out in that area with one-design elements being introduced to make a more even fleet.</p> <p>And while Team New Zealand continue to search every salty corner of the globe to try to uncover the millions needed to stay on course, Barker will have the luxury of putting his hand out to Team Japan's benefactor, SoftBank boss Masoyashi Son, whose wealth is estimated to be US$22 billion (NZ$29b), making him Japan's wealthiest man.</p> <p>Masoyashi hasn't entered this game to make up the numbers. He is serious about trying to win the America's Cup and the hiring of Barker is another sign of that.</p> <p>Barker knows the ins and outs of this game as well as anyone going around at the moment. He will be desperate to make the most of this unexpected second chance. It's a silver lining to the darkest time of his storied career.&nbsp;You can also bet Barker is being paid handsomely for his efforts – undoubtedly far more than his undisclosed salary with the Kiwi syndicate.</p> <p>Money won't win the America's Cup… but it sure helps. Just ask the last two men to have their hands on the Auld Mug – Swiss billionaire Ernesto Bertarelli, who hijacked Kiwi talent to man his successful Alinghi team, and Larry Ellison, one of the world's richest men who enticed New Zealand's greatest Cup sailor, Sir Russell Coutts, to oversee his successful challenge and subsequent defence.</p> <p>Sound familiar?</p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816735,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154555+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:45 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Getty Images\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Dean Barker has already got a look at the Bermuda setup for the next Americas Cup.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816735,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179955/735/11816735.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816736,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154555+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:45 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Getty Images\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Dean Barker has already got a look at the Bermuda setup for the next Americas Cup.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816736,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179955/736/11816736.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"620\",\n                            \"height\": \"349\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816737,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154555+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:45 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Getty Images\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Dean Barker has already got a look at the Bermuda setup for the next Americas Cup.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816737,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179955/737/11816737.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"200\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816738,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179955/738/11816738.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816739,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154555+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:45 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Getty Images\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Dean Barker has already got a look at the Bermuda setup for the next Americas Cup.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816739,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179955/739/11816739.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"219\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816740,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154555+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:45 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Getty Images\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Dean Barker has already got a look at the Bermuda setup for the next Americas Cup.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816740,\n                            \"layout\": \"ipad section splash 956:956\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432179955/740/11816740.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"956\",\n                            \"height\": \"956\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68739063,\n            \"path\": \"/business/68739063/Southern-Cross-confirms-cable-cut\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/business/68739063/Southern-Cross-confirms-cable-cut\",\n            \"section\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"section-home\": \"Business\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Business\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-image\",\n            \"title\": \"Southern Cross confirms cable cut\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Southern Cross cable cut\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T142039+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"14:20 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"TOM PULLAR-STRECKER\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/business/68739063\",\n            \"intro\": \"New Zealand's internet connection to the United States may be dangling by a thread.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"New Zealand's internet connection to the United States may be dangling by a thread.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>New Zealand's internet connection to the United States may be dangling by a thread.</p> <p>Southern Cross Cable Network confirmed a segment of its cable network between Oregon and San Jose in the United States was cut at about 1am New Zealand time by a contractor working for the state's transport department.</p> <p>Southern Cross spokeswoman Rosemay Foot said repairs had been underway but she was unable to confirm if they had been completed.</p> <p>A document tweeted by Auckland telecommunications executive Liam Farr indicated the cut had required internet traffic between the US and Australia to be re-routed via New Zealand.</p> <p>Foot was unable to confirm that. However, if the report is correct, it appears possible a further cable cut could have compromised New Zealand's communications with the rest of the world.</p> <p>Southern Cross' network is configured as a &quot;figure of eight&quot; centred on Hawaii and is designed so there is always a back-up route if one section of the cable is cut.</p> <p>The land-based &quot;E2&quot; segment of the cable that runs between Oregon and San Jose has an addition terrestrial back-up, however, making it unclear why international traffic would have required re-routing. Further comment has been sought from Southern Cross.</p> <p>Foot said New Zealand customers of Southern Cross had not been affected by the cable cut and nor had other customers who had paid for capacity via a back-up route.</p> <p>However, it had had some impact on customers outside New Zealand who had not paid for &quot;protected circuits&quot;. &nbsp;</p> <p>Southern Cross Cable Network confirmed the incident several hours after it was first approached by Stuff for comment.</p> <p>Several attempts have been made to build a business case for an additional fibre-optic cable that would link New Zealand to the US and reduce the country's reliance on Southern Cross.</p> <p>Hawaiki Cable secured a carrier licence in April from Communications Minister Amy Adams for its proposed subsea cable that would run between Sydney, Whangarei and Oregon.</p> <p>However, it has yet to confirm it has secured the US$300 million ($410m) in funding that it needs to begin construction.</p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816297,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150729+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:07 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"iStock\",\n                    \"caption\": \"A cable cut in Oregon has put the fragility of New Zealand's internet connections back under the spotlight.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816297,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432177649/297/11816297.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816298,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150729+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:07 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"iStock\",\n                    \"caption\": \"A cable cut in Oregon has put the fragility of New Zealand's internet connections back under the spotlight.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816298,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432177649/298/11816298.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"620\",\n                            \"height\": \"349\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816299,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150729+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:07 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"iStock\",\n                    \"caption\": \"A cable cut in Oregon has put the fragility of New Zealand's internet connections back under the spotlight.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816299,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432177649/299/11816299.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"200\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816300,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432177649/300/11816300.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816301,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150729+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:07 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"iStock\",\n                    \"caption\": \"A cable cut in Oregon has put the fragility of New Zealand's internet connections back under the spotlight.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816301,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432177649/301/11816301.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"219\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816302,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150729+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:07 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"iStock\",\n                    \"caption\": \"A cable cut in Oregon has put the fragility of New Zealand's internet connections back under the spotlight.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816302,\n                            \"layout\": \"ipad section splash 956:956\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432177649/302/11816302.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"956\",\n                            \"height\": \"956\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68746469,\n            \"path\": \"/travel/travel-troubles/68746469/Sweet-16-birthday-party-spoiled-by-surprise-from-the-sky\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/travel/travel-troubles/68746469/Sweet-16-birthday-party-spoiled-by-surprise-from-the-sky\",\n            \"section\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"section-home\": \"Travel Troubles\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Travel\",\n            \"layout\": \"a-standard\",\n            \"title\": \"Sweet 16 birthday party spoiled by surprise from the sky\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Sweet 16 spoiled by smelly surprise\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154304+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"15:43 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": null,\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/travel/travel-troubles/68746469\",\n            \"intro\": \"An American girl had a not-so-sweet 16th birthday celebration when it rained poo on her party. \",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"A teen's birthday celebration was soiled when poo rained down from the sky.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>An American girl had a not-so-sweet 16th birthday celebration when it rained poo on her party.&nbsp;</p> <p>Jacinda Cambray and her family and friends were enjoying themselves in the backyard of the Cambray's Pennsylvania home when faeces rained down upon them.</p> <p>&quot;Out of nowhere, from the sky, comes a bunch of feces[sic], lands on her,&quot; <b><a href=\\\"http://www.myfoxdetroit.com/story/29097193/local-girl\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Joe Cambray, Jacinda's stepfather told FOX 29.<br /> <br /> </a></b>&quot;We just got done with cake. Thank God. We took the cake back in, because within two minutes, something fell from the sky. It was brown, it was everywhere, it got on everything,&quot; Joe Cambray said to<b>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.myfoxdetroit.com/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">myfoxdetroit.com</a></b></p> <p>A quick look at a travel app on a smartphone showed there were five planes currently flying above the residence.</p> <p>According to the FAA, all aircraft are required to dispose of waste at an airport and according to<b> <a href=\\\"http://www.slate.com/articles/news_and_politics/explainer/2012/02/long_island_couple_pelted_with_poo_where_do_airplanes_dump_their_waste_.html\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Slate.com</a></b>, they&nbsp;can't rain down poo on a neighbourhood even if they wanted to.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;Under normal circumstances, the ground crew disposes of the sewage after the plane lands. Even if the pilot and flight attendants wanted to empty a tank midflight, they couldn't, as the valve is located on the outside of the plane, and can only be opened by the ground crew.</p> <p>The family has filed a complaint and the US&nbsp;Federal Aviation Administration is investigating the incident.&nbsp;</p> <p>If ever there was an appropriate song for faeces falling from the sky, it would have to be this:&nbsp;</p> <p><iframe width=\\\"618\\\" height=\\\"464\\\" src=\\\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EwTZ2xpQwpA\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\">&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;nbsp;</iframe></p><p><iframe width=\\\"618\\\" height=\\\"348\\\" src=\\\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/h6G1qdm8zdA\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p><blockquote class=\\\"twitter-tweet\\\" lang=\\\"en\\\"><p lang=\\\"en\\\" dir=\\\"ltr\\\">How to ruin a Sweet 16 Party? Plane releases its &quot;bathroom contents&quot; above them! Story at 10 on <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/FOX29philly\\\">@FOX29philly</a> <a href=\\\"http://t.co/65N8dqQPvA\\\">pic.twitter.com/65N8dqQPvA</a></p>&mdash; Brad Sattin (@BradSattin) <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/BradSattin/status/600456021694373888\\\">May 19, 2015</a></blockquote> <script async src=\\\"http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\\\" charset=\\\"utf-8\\\"></script></p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817189,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T162217+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:22 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"youtube\",\n                    \"caption\": \"An American girl had a not so sweet 16th birthday celebration when rained poo on her party.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817189,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182137/189/11817189.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"59\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817190,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T162217+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:22 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"youtube\",\n                    \"caption\": \"An American girl had a not so sweet 16th birthday celebration when rained poo on her party.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817190,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182137/190/11817190.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"200\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817191,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182137/191/11817191.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817192,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T162217+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:22 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"youtube\",\n                    \"caption\": \"An American girl had a not so sweet 16th birthday celebration when rained poo on her party.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817192,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182137/192/11817192.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"220\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68750151,\n            \"path\": \"/entertainment/tv-radio/68750151/The-sad-end-of-John-Campbell\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/entertainment/tv-radio/68750151/The-sad-end-of-John-Campbell\",\n            \"section\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"section-home\": \"TV & Radio\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Entertainment\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-video\",\n            \"title\": \"The sad end of John Campbell\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"The sad end of John Campbell\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T163706+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"16:37 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"JANE BOWRON\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"intro\": \"With cynical timing MediaWorks lowered the boom on John Campbell effectively giving him his marching orders at the same time as the Budget came out.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"With cynical timing MediaWorks lowered the boom, effectively giving John Campbell his marching orders at the same time Budget came out.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>With cynical timing MediaWorks lowered the boom on John Campbell effectively giving him his marching orders at the same time as the Budget came out.</p> <p>Obviously hoping the axing of <i>Campbell Live</i>&nbsp; would be eclipsed by Bill English's Thursday afternoon Budget, MediaWorks announced the decision when the focus was elsewhere. But the&nbsp;news hit hard. Elvis had left the building, and a four-day-a-week show with two co-presenters would&nbsp;replace him.<br /> <br /> <b>READ MORE:&nbsp;<br /> * <a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/tv-radio/68739990/john-campbell-to-leave-tv3\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Cambell to leave TV3</a><br /> *&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/tv-radio/68742753/sadness-and-anger-as-underdog-john-campbell-bows-out\\\">Sadness and anger as 'underdog' John Campbell bows out<br /> </a>*&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/68747016/so-where-to-from-here-for-campbell-live-and-what-next-for-john-campbell\\\">So where to from here for Campbell Live? And what next for John Campbell?<br /> </a>*&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/tv-radio/67945132/The-numbers-behind-Campbell-Live\\\">The numbers behind Campbell Live<br /> </a>*&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/dominion-post/culture/television/8170752/John-Campbell-The-Jolly-Journo\\\">John Campbell: The Jolly Journo<br /> <br /> </a></b>He was offered a co-host position, but Campbell said no. Who can blame the host who has been at the helm for more than&nbsp;a decade? It would have been too humiliating to stay on in a show that previously bore your name on it, the Campbell brand having stood for something as it fought for the underdog and took on a Government that over the last few years consistently turned down numerous invitations to appear on the show to battle it out with the passionate host.</p> <p>Six weeks ago, when the axing of the show was first raised, fans rushed to its aid, parking bums on seats and demonstrating their loyalty as the ratings started to top the 6pm news bulletin. But the writing was on the wall as the show was rumoured to be too pink in its persuasion by friends of John Key, high up in the echelons of MediaWorks.</p> <p>The review was led by TV3's current affairs boss, Mark Jennings. Senior management were unanimous in the decision to side-line Campbell. By opting for co-hosts - the search having already started for fresh presenters - it indicates the new format may try and give Seven Sharp (and its signature blathering, banter and editorialising by their boy-girl presenter line-up) a run for its money.</p> <p>Campbell's passion for the job can never be doubted, as he crusaded for so many causes and issues that faced everyday New Zealanders; kids' lunches in school, child poverty, changing the drink-driving laws, raising money for the victims of natural disasters, and tirelessly battling away for the quake-affected in Christchurch.</p> <p>MediaWorks, having recently gone all out on the multimedia Paul Henry show that is failing to gain traction, has ditched a household name and angered Campbell Live's loyal fan base who won't take this lying down.</p> <p>Ten years ago, Campbell Live entered the scene as a compassionate, deeper thinking alternative to the Holmes show and stood its ground. Recent moves by MediaWorks&nbsp;to become the emperors of reality TV meant that Campbell Live became a strange fit for them.</p> <p>What is sad is that the host leaves without a well-deserved, decent send off for his services to the nation.</p> <p>Some found his over-the-top sincerity irksome, but he could not have retained that front for a decade without it being the real deal. No doubt he will resurface elsewhere. If I was Kathryn Ryan, I would be very afraid.</p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817338,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T163732+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:37 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"caption\": \"*\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817338,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432183052/338/11817338.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817339,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T163732+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:37 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Michael Bradley/ Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"sunday-star-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Sunday Star Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"12.09.2008 John Campbell on the new set for TV3 News and his show Campbell Live in Auckland. Photo Credit Michael Bradley. 12/09/2008 91414 Michael Bradley Auckland This is the property of the Sunday Star-Times\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817339,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432183052/339/11817339.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817340,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T163732+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:37 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Michael Bradley/ Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"sunday-star-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Sunday Star Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"12.09.2008 John Campbell on the new set for TV3 News and his show Campbell Live in Auckland. Photo Credit Michael Bradley. 12/09/2008 91414 Michael Bradley Auckland This is the property of the Sunday Star-Times\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817340,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432183052/340/11817340.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"620\",\n                            \"height\": \"348\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817341,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T163732+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:37 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Michael Bradley/ Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"sunday-star-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Sunday Star Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"12.09.2008 John Campbell on the new set for TV3 News and his show Campbell Live in Auckland. Photo Credit Michael Bradley. 12/09/2008 91414 Michael Bradley Auckland This is the property of the Sunday Star-Times\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817341,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432183052/341/11817341.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"199\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817342,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432183052/342/11817342.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817343,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T163732+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:37 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Michael Bradley/ Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"sunday-star-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Sunday Star Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"12.09.2008 John Campbell on the new set for TV3 News and his show Campbell Live in Auckland. Photo Credit Michael Bradley. 12/09/2008 91414 Michael Bradley Auckland This is the property of the Sunday Star-Times\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817343,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432183052/343/11817343.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"220\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817344,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T163732+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:37 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Michael Bradley/ Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"sunday-star-times\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Sunday Star Times\",\n                    \"caption\": \"12.09.2008 John Campbell on the new set for TV3 News and his show Campbell Live in Auckland. Photo Credit Michael Bradley. 12/09/2008 91414 Michael Bradley Auckland This is the property of the Sunday Star-Times\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11817344,\n                            \"layout\": \"ipad section splash 956:956\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432183052/344/11817344.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"956\",\n                            \"height\": \"956\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ],\n            \"videos\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816936,\n                    \"layout\": \"Standard Video\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"aap\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"AAP\",\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T160031+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:00 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Youtube\",\n                    \"caption\": \"John Campbell is leaving TV3, with Mediaworks replacing Campbell Live with a relaunched current affairs show four nights a week.\",\n                    \"src\": \"http://file2.stuff.co.nz/1432180831/937/11816937.mp4\",\n                    \"video_poster\": {\n                        \"id\": 11816938,\n                        \"layout\": \"Video Image\",\n                        \"src\": \"http://file2.stuff.co.nz/1432183053/938/11816938.jpg\",\n                        \"width\": \"640\",\n                        \"height\": \"360\"\n                    }\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68732748,\n            \"path\": \"/national/crime/68732748/Blessie-Gotingco-trial-Murder-accuseds-story-unusual-defence-says\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/national/crime/68732748/Blessie-Gotingco-trial-Murder-accuseds-story-unusual-defence-says\",\n            \"section\": \"National\",\n            \"section-home\": \"Crime\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"National\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-image\",\n            \"title\": \"Blessie Gotingco trial: Murder accused's story 'unusual', defence says\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Blessie trial: Accused's story 'unusual' \",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155434+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"15:54 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"KELLY DENNETT\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"intro\": \"The lawyer of the man accused of killing Blessie Gotingco has told a jury his client's story is \\\"unusual\\\" but that he didn't rape or murder Gotingco. \",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"Carrying out a murder in an GPS bracelet would be 'inexplicable' and 'stupid', defence says. \",\n            \"body\": \"<p>The lawyer of the man accused of killing Blessie Gotingco has told a jury his client's story is &quot;unusual&quot; but that he didn't rape or murder Gotingco.&nbsp;</p> <p>Chris Wilkinson-Smith has begun summing up the defence case at the High Court at Auckland on Thursday, shortly after being reinstated as a lawyer, after the accused fired him four weeks ago.&nbsp;</p> <p><b>READ MORE:</b></p> <p><b>*&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/national/crime/68699307/blessie-gotingco-trial-jury-member-a-noshow\\\">Jury member a no-show</a></b></p> <p><b>*&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/national/crime/68666214/blessie-gotingco-trial-murder-accused-cries-in-court\\\">Murder accused admits stabbing</a></b></p> <p>Wilkinson-Smith said crown prosectors had presented &quot;uncontested&quot; evidence and witnesses that supported the defence case.&nbsp;</p> <p>The 28-year-old accused maintains he was driving down Salisbury Rd on the night of May 24 last year, looking for drugs, when he accidentally struck Gotingco as she walked home from a bus stop, Wilkinson-Smith said. &nbsp;</p> <p>Panicking, the accused claims he put her in his car to take her back to his Birkdale apartment and believing she was dead, stabbed her in order to make her look like the victim of a murder, rather than a road accident.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;This was an accident, members of the jury, not a deliberate running down,&quot; Wilkinson-Smith said.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;What happened, the cause of that accident, was maybe a young driver or an inexperienced driver driving too quickly, but it's not a deliberate act of violence, or using a car as a weapon.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;Of course what happens next is unusual. To explain what he did next you really have to know a bit about his situation. He says he panicked. He was high on meth, and it altered his thinking. He's also on a bracelet. He's also five minutes away from being able to get back to his house for his curfew.&quot;&nbsp;</p> <p>He pointed to parts of the crown's case that didn't &quot;gel&quot;, including prosecutor's &quot;inexplicable&quot; suggestion that the accused would plan a murder, knowing full well he was being tracked electronically.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;Why would anybody wearing an electronic bracelet that tracks your movement all through the day, plan a murder that can be plotted on aerial photographs? Does that make sense?&quot; Wilkinson-Smith asked. &nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;How stupid would you have to be to lay your plans to do an abduction and murder and not make any plans for the fact you're wearing a GPS bracelet?&quot;&nbsp;</p> <p>The fact the collision was proved to have happened just minutes before the defendant's curfew expired was proof it was an accident, he said.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;Methamphetamine is a huge part of what happened next.&quot;</p> <p>Wilkinson-Smith said he didn't expect jurors to &quot;feel sorry&quot; for his client but asked them to put themselves in his client's shoes.&nbsp;</p> <p>Hurrying to get home after searching for drugs, and then hitting an innocent pedestrian had put the accused into a panic, he said.&nbsp;</p> <p>Previously the court had heard from another driver on Salisbury Rd, who said they had swerved to avoid hitting Gotingco whom they claimed was standing in the middle of the street.&nbsp;</p> <p>After checking in the rear vision mirror, Junior Anau noticed the BMW that had previously been tail gating him had come to a stop.&nbsp;</p> <p>Wilkinson-Smith said this was evidence that supported the defendant's version of events.&nbsp;</p> <p>Wilkinson-Smith argued the GPS evidence showing the accused moving around Eskdale Cemetery prior to allegedly abducting Gotingco was &quot;nowhere near accurate enough&quot;.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;These dots are just estimates of his position and they're up to 100m out,&quot; he said.</p> <p>He criticised the storage of DNA samples that had been exposed to condensation, and said it was possible cross contamination had occurred from a sperm-stained sheet wrapping Gotingco's body, or from stains on the back seat of the car.&nbsp;</p> <p><b>VICTIM WAS 'VERY MUCH ALIVE', PROSECUTOR SAYS</b></p> <p>Prosecutor Kieran Raftery summed up the crown's case at the final day of the trial of the man accused of killing Blessie Gotingco.&nbsp;</p> <p>The 28-year old has pleaded not guilty to raping and murdering Gotingco on May 24 last year, despite admitting stabbing her after hitting her with his BMW.&nbsp;</p> <p>On Thursday Raftery began by pointing to evidence from two Salisbury Rd residents, one from a young girl who heard a high pitched scream shortly before 8pm, and another who heard a car idling outside her window where debris was later found.&nbsp;</p> <p>He pointed out that the scream didn't come until after a car could be heard stopping and idling on the street, showing Gotingco was &quot;very much alive&quot; after the impact of the accident, and certainly when she was bundled into the accused's car, he said.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;He knew from that moment on she was alive,&quot; Raftery said.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;To scream, you have to be very much alive. If [the witness] heard the scream, the man outside bundling her into his car would have heard the scream.</p> <p>&quot;If the crown scenario is correct, he was actually abducting someone for the purposes of raping her. He doesn't want someone who is dead, he wants someone who is very much alive.&quot;&nbsp;</p> <p>Raftery said it was &quot;highly odd&quot; that the accused had spent time in not just one, but two cemeteries, on the day Gotingco disappeared and later was found in Eskdale Cemetery.&nbsp;</p> <p>GPS movements showed he'd spent time at Eskdale Cemetery, allegedly smoking drugs, before later going to Birkenhead Cemetery where he claimed he was spending time looking at a map to figure out where Salisbury Rd was.&nbsp;</p> <p>This was the street where a &quot;man whose name he never learned&quot; allegedly told him he could score drugs, Raftery said, pointing out that the accused never bothered to go to a second street in Beach Haven where he was also told he could score.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;First of all, just thinking about it, it's just highly odd that he should go to another cemetery, when he'd just inspected one for 10 or 12 minutes and the dots tell you he's moving about within that cemetery, moving around,&quot; Raftery said.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;The (other) address he'd been given, he goes nowhere near. What does that suggest? It's a lot of nonsense. It's a story, as is the whole of his story, made up to try and fit with the evidence.&quot;&nbsp;</p> <p>The defendant alleged striking Gotingco had been an accident and he stabbed her because he believed she was already dead, and wanted it to look as if she was the victim of a random attack, in order to avoid detection.&nbsp;</p> <p>Raftery said how Gotingco came to be in the accused's garage, where he took her after hitting her, was &quot;technically irrelevant&quot; but it formed an important narrative to what ensued next.&nbsp;</p> <p>Salisbury Rd, where Gotingco got off a bus at 7.50pm, was not well lit: &quot;It's quite a good street to pick a victim.&quot;&nbsp;</p> <p>Raftery said the real reason he'd taken Gotingco back to his home could be found in the physical evidence taken from Gotingco and the garage.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;His semen was found inside her vagina. That, more than anything else, tells you why she was taken to that garage - because he wanted to have sex with her. That's why he took her there. Why else is that semen inside her?&quot; Raftery said.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;He says it's got there by police malpractice, an unidentified police officer, but you can imagine who they must be - people responsible for the search of his premises.&quot;&nbsp;</p> <p>However the police and forensic scientists would have to be &quot;particularly devious&quot; to create a fake medical kit, collect semen from the accused's apartment, and then give the swabs to the pathologist.</p> <p>He said &quot;a number of people must have put their heads together&quot; for the accused's accusation to have been true.</p> <p>Despite just a trace amount of semen found inside Gotingco's body, Raftery said it didn't matter if it was &quot;one sperm head, or 1001. There was sperm there, and it was his&quot;.&nbsp;</p> <p>There was no suggestion that Gotingco had been raped after she died, and therefore she must have been alive, Raftery said.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;I am accusing (the defendant) of some very serious crimes but I'm not accusing him of necrophilia,&quot; he said. &nbsp;</p> <p>Raftery finished his address by pointing to GPS evidence that showed the accused had spent the rest of the night going backwards and forwards between his garage and his apartment.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;Far from being what he claims, a quick three minutes, lots of stab wounds to make it look like a murder and then I go upstairs and have a rest and go to bed. He was very busy, because he had a number of things to do,&quot; Raftery said.&nbsp;</p> <p>That included tidying the garage, cleaning himself and disposing of the evidence.&nbsp;</p> <p>A knife was later found buried in the back garden and despite another fish filleting knife with blood on the sheath found in the kitchen, Raftery said, &quot;it doesn't actually matter&quot; which knife was used.&nbsp;</p> <p>He said Gotingco's stab wounds, some to her front and back, showed she was probably struggling at the time she was stabbed.&nbsp;</p> <p>&quot;This woman was very much alive when he raped her, he knew it. Those wounds were inflicted as a way to finish her off so she could never speak,&quot; Raftery closed.&nbsp;</p> <p>The court room has remained packed for the final day of the trial, with Gotingco's family and friends attending for closing remarks.&nbsp;</p> <p><b>NURSE'S TESTIMONY</b></p> <p>Earlier, the murder accused rehired his lawyers for what is likely to be the last day of the trial.&nbsp;</p> <p>Chris Wilkinson-Smith and Kevin Brosnahan were appointed court amicus instead but on Thursday Justice Timothy Brewer told the jury of 12 that the defendant had chosen to rehire his lawyers after legal aid was approved.&nbsp;</p> <p>On Thursday morning the defence team called their last witness, a nurse who visited the accused while he was in prison last year.&nbsp;</p> <p>Her name and place of work is suppressed.&nbsp;</p> <p>She testified that the accused had told her was &quot;coming down&quot; after being a daily user of methamphetamine and cannabis.&nbsp;</p> <p>Despite claiming to be a drug addict who was high at the time of Gotingco's death, crown prosecutor Kieran Raftery said there was no evidence of drugs or drug paraphernalia being in his car or his apartment.&nbsp;</p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816876,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155504+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:55 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Lawrence Smith\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The man accused of murdering Blessie Gotingco appears in the High Court in Auckland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816876,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180504/876/11816876.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"59\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816877,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155504+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:55 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Lawrence Smith\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The man accused of murdering Blessie Gotingco appears in the High Court in Auckland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816877,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180504/877/11816877.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"620\",\n                            \"height\": \"349\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816878,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155504+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:55 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Lawrence Smith\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The man accused of murdering Blessie Gotingco appears in the High Court in Auckland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816878,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180504/878/11816878.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"200\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816879,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180504/879/11816879.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816880,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155504+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:55 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Lawrence Smith\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The man accused of murdering Blessie Gotingco appears in the High Court in Auckland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816880,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180504/880/11816880.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"220\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816881,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155505+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:55 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Lawrence Smith\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The man accused of murdering Blessie Gotingco appears in the High Court in Auckland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816881,\n                            \"layout\": \"ipad section splash 956:956\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180505/881/11816881.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"956\",\n                            \"height\": \"956\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816882,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155505+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:55 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Supplied\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Blessie Gotingco.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816882,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180505/882/11816882.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"238\",\n                            \"height\": \"286\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68703415,\n            \"path\": \"/business/68703415/Budget-2015-Almost-1-billion-from-state-asset-sales-goes-on-new-spending\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/business/68703415/Budget-2015-Almost-1-billion-from-state-asset-sales-goes-on-new-spending\",\n            \"section\": \"Politics\",\n            \"section-home\": \"Business\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Business\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-video\",\n            \"title\": \"Budget 2015: Almost $1 billion from state asset sales goes on new spending\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"$1 billion Budget spendup\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155313+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"15:53 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"HAMISH RUTHERFORD\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/business/68703415\",\n            \"intro\": \"Almost a billion dollars from state asset sales goes into new spending programmes in the Budget, from a top-up of KiwiRail to an extension of the broadband network and even a new wharf for the Chatham Islands.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"Almost a billion dollars from state asset sales goes into new spending programmes.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>Almost a billion dollars from state asset sales goes into new spending programmes in the Budget, from a top-up of KiwiRail to an extension of the broadband network and even a new wharf for the Chatham Islands.</p> <p>After raising around $4.7b from partial sales of three energy companies and Air New Zealand, the Government used the proceeds to establish the Future Investment Fund.</p> <p>Although the political messaging said the funds would be used for investments such as &quot;schools and hospitals&quot;, the net is being spread to include a wide variety of projects.</p> <p>Thursday's Budget confirmed that KiwiRail, the loss-making state owned rail company, will receive $210 million this year along with a &quot;pre-commitment&quot; of a further $190m for 2016.</p> <p><b>READ MORE:</b></p> <p><b>* <a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/budget-2015.html\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Full Budget coverage</a></b></p> <p><b>* <a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/68741678/budget-2015-modest-tax-cuts-flagged-for-2017\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">English flags modest tax cuts</a></b></p> <p><b>* <a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/68702261/budget-2015-national-makes-some-concessions-but-also-gets-tough\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">The carrot and stick Budget</a></b></p> <p>English described the cash as an &quot;equity injection&quot; although the Government already owns 100 per cent of the state owned enterprise. While he said the use of the fund was &quot;appropriate&quot; he signalled Kiwirail would have to take steps to eliminate the need for ongoing subsidy.</p> <p>&quot;We imagined three or four years ago that we wouldn't be putting, that KiwiRail wouldn't require so much ongoing investment. As we have said here...that level of government contribution is unsustainable at $200m per year to keep the operation going.&quot;</p> <p>Already announced, the Budget also confirms that another $210m will be invested in the ultra fast broadband network, as well as $97m for regional highways and 440m towards regional cycleways.</p> <p>New projects announced on Thursday include $52m for a total rebuild of the Waitangi Wharf in the Chatham Islands.</p> <p>&quot;The wharf is the only cargo-handling facility for essential supplies, including diesel for the electricity grid and fuel for air services,&quot; Internal Affairs Minister Peter Dunne said.</p> <p>&quot;The existing wharf is a structural risk and needs to be replaced within five years.&quot;</p> <p>Other projects winning funding include $40m for capital investment at Te Papa on its Wellington buildings and $13m to relocate Archives New Zealand's Christchurch regional office.</p> <p>Following the spending, around $726m is left in the fund, although $190m of this has already been earmarked for KiwiRail. The fund is expected to be completely exhausted in the 2016 Budget.</p> <p>Elsewhere biosecurity funding will be boosted by $24.9m over the next four years, including for additional x-ray machines for screening the increasing number of passengers entering New Zealand.</p> <p>A further $4.7m will be spent over four years on more customs officials, this time for passengers leaving the country, in a bid to maintain New Zealand's low risk security status.</p> <p>Both measures, and much of the cost of the existing border programmes, will be covered from a new $100m tax on international travel.</p> <p>In housing, a new $52.2m contingency fund has been established to help facilitate building on Crown-owned land in Auckland, which would sold off after construction, including a &quot;portion&quot; of affordable housing.</p> <p>&quot;Our aim is to have a signed development agreement for the first land parcel within six months.&quot;</p> <p>Revenue Minister Todd McClay has announced new plans to write off large amounts of child support debt in a bid to recover more of the payments owed to the Crown.</p> <p>Currently child support debt is $3.2b and rising, and only $700m of that is actual child support, with the rest penalties for late payments. More than $800m is owed by people living in Australia.</p> <p>McClay said over the next four years around $1.7b of the debt wold be forgiven &quot;to encourage more support to reach children&quot;.</p> <p>&quot;Liable parents are facing paralysing levels of debt from penalties, and as a result are not attempting to pay their outstanding amount, nor are they meeting their current obligations.&quot;</p> <p>Inland Revenue would &quot;adopt a 'fair and reasonable' test to consider applying penalty relief where it makes sense to do so&quot;.</p> <p>Other changes are being made to cut the amount IRD charges in future penalties, from 10 per cent immediately, to 2 per cent immediately and a further 8 per cent on payments which are more than seven days late.</p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816842,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155232+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:52 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Finance Minister Bill English delivers the Budget 2015 announcing an changes to Kiwi Saver, benefits and border security.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816842,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180437/842/11816842.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816870,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155357+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:53 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"JEFF TOLLAN/Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"fairfax-media\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Fairfax Media\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Bill English on delivering the Budget confirmed KiwiRail will receive $210 million this year.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816870,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180437/870/11816870.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816871,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155357+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:53 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"JEFF TOLLAN/Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"fairfax-media\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Fairfax Media\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Bill English on delivering the Budget confirmed KiwiRail will receive $210 million this year.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816871,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180437/871/11816871.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"620\",\n                            \"height\": \"349\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816872,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155358+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:53 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"JEFF TOLLAN/Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"fairfax-media\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Fairfax Media\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Bill English on delivering the Budget confirmed KiwiRail will receive $210 million this year.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816872,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180438/872/11816872.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"200\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816873,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180438/873/11816873.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816874,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155358+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:53 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"JEFF TOLLAN/Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"fairfax-media\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Fairfax Media\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Bill English on delivering the Budget confirmed KiwiRail will receive $210 million this year.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816874,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180438/874/11816874.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"220\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816875,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155358+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:53 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Alex Liu/Fairfax NZ\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The Beehive and the statue of Richard John Seddon in Wellington.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816875,\n                            \"layout\": \"ipad section splash 956:956\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180438/875/11816875.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"956\",\n                            \"height\": \"956\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ],\n            \"videos\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816395,\n                    \"layout\": \"Standard Video\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"aap\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"AAP\",\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T151532+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:15 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Parliament TV\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Finance Minister Bill English delivers the Budget 2015 announcing an changes to Kiwi Saver, benefits and border security.\",\n                    \"src\": \"http://file2.stuff.co.nz/1432178132/396/11816396.mp4\",\n                    \"video_poster\": {\n                        \"id\": 11816397,\n                        \"layout\": \"Video Image\",\n                        \"src\": \"http://file2.stuff.co.nz/1432180634/397/11816397.jpg\",\n                        \"width\": \"640\",\n                        \"height\": \"360\"\n                    }\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68729555,\n            \"path\": \"/sport/football/68729555/Taranaki-footballers-put-on-good-behaviour-bond\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/sport/football/68729555/Taranaki-footballers-put-on-good-behaviour-bond\",\n            \"section\": \"Football\",\n            \"section-home\": \"News\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Taranaki Daily News\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-image\",\n            \"title\": \"Taranaki footballers put on good behaviour bond \",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Play nice or pay up\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154708+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"15:47 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"LEIGHTON KEITH\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/taranaki-daily-news/news/68729555\",\n            \"intro\": \"Taranaki football clubs have been told to play nice or pay up as referees face an increase in abuse from players.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"Footballers put on $1k good behaviour bond after referee abuse rises.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>Taranaki football clubs have been told to play nice or pay up as referees face an increase in abuse from players.</p> <p>This week Central Football's eastern operations manager Phil Holt announced all clubs would be subject to a good behaviour bond in an attempt to stamp out ugly incidents involving officials in the beautiful game.&nbsp;</p> <p>The move could see Central Football clubs - from Taranaki to Manawatu and the Hawke's Bay - hit with a $1000 fine if they received a second match report citing persistent questioning of match officials, surrounding of the referee and unruly behaviour by teams.</p> <p>&quot;It's right across our Federation, it's not just the one area,&quot; Holt said.</p> <p>&quot;It's just a general thing because we've been receiving reports from refs about the constant snipping by snide comments by players about the ref and their decision making.&quot;</p> <p>The measure has been met with approval from Taranaki clubs.</p> <p>&quot;The point is we are having that much referee abuse of late that we will end up with no referees if this continues,&quot; Holt said.</p> <p>Top level Taranaki referee Andy McGechan said the bond was a very good idea as there was a huge problem recruiting and retaining officials.</p> <p>&quot;A lot of that is because the young people that we try to encourage to take up the whistle find it a little bit too daunting at times because of the descent and the back chat and the abuse from players and parents on the sideline,&quot; he said.</p> <p>McGechan said he had issued two yellow cards at secondary school matches this week due to back chat.</p> <p>&quot;It happens all of the time.&quot;</p> <p>Holt said while it wasn't a major problem he agreed it was taking its toll on some of the younger match officials, especially females.</p> <p>&quot;There probably has been a few more incidents of it this season, in the past years it hasn't been quite as bad.</p> <p>&quot;We are talking about young refs, teenagers, who we are trying to bring into the game. It's easy for them to be put off.&quot;</p> <p>Holt said he knew one referee who was reconsidering their future in the sport.</p> <p>It was the first time an across the board good behaviour bond had been imposed in the region.</p> <p>Every case would be judged on merit and the organisation would investigate any bad behaviour before action was taken.</p> <p>&quot;I'm sure that these clubs will get this message through to their players - if you do step out of line this is what we are going to get.&quot;</p> <p>New Plymouth Rangers Football Club president Monty Ammundsen said he agreed with the move and the consequences of breaking the bond would be emphasised to players.</p> <p>&quot;I think it's necessary, some club teams need to have a good look at their behaviour on the field,&quot; Ammundsen said.</p> <p>&quot;Some of the stuff that goes on is really unacceptable.&quot;</p> <p>Moturoa Associated Football Club president Stephen Frowde said although the club didn't condone bad behaviour he hadn't come across any this season.</p> <p>Frowde said the sport needed good referees but he believed $1000 was a &quot;massive amount&quot; of money for any club.</p> <p>&quot;They certainly need to do something if that kind of conduct is happening but I don't think penalising clubs financially is a positive way of doing it,&quot; he said.</p> <p>&quot;A club like us wouldn't be able to afford that sort of fine.&quot;</p> \",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816818,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155110+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:51 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Phillip Rollo\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Wakefield's Dylyn Pellowe looked askance at the ref when shown a red card during their division one football match in Southland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816818,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180270/818/11816818.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"59\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816819,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155110+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:51 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Phillip Rollo\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Wakefield's Dylyn Pellowe looked askance at the ref when shown a red card during their division one football match in Southland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816819,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180270/819/11816819.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"620\",\n                            \"height\": \"349\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816820,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155111+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:51 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Phillip Rollo\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Wakefield's Dylyn Pellowe looked askance at the ref when shown a red card during their division one football match in Southland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816820,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180271/820/11816820.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300\",\n                            \"height\": \"199\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816821,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180271/821/11816821.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816822,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155111+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:51 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Phillip Rollo\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Wakefield's Dylyn Pellowe looked askance at the ref when shown a red card during their division one football match in Southland.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816822,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180271/822/11816822.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"418\",\n                            \"height\": \"220\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68738749,\n            \"path\": \"/national/68738749/Burst-pipe-floods-Redcliffs-Christchurch\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/national/68738749/Burst-pipe-floods-Redcliffs-Christchurch\",\n            \"section\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"section-home\": \"News\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"The Press\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-video\",\n            \"title\": \"Burst pipe floods Redcliffs, Christchurch\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Burst pipe floods streets\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154624+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"15:46 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"BRITTANY MANN\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/the-press/news/68738749\",\n            \"intro\": \"A burst water main flooded streets and properties in Redcliffs, Christchurch on Wednesday.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"Streets and properties have been flooded in Redcliffs, Christchurch, after water main was gouged.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>A burst water main flooded streets and properties in Redcliffs, Christchurch on Wednesday.</p> <p>Emergency and city services pumped thousands of litres of&nbsp;water from the estuary side of Main Rd, after a mill used by Fulton Hogan&nbsp;to lay a new road gouged a mains pipe near the Redcliffs Shops about 11.30am.</p> <p>Some residents had water flowing into their garages and through their properties to the sea on the other side.</p> <p>Firefighters from Woolston and Sumner helped pump water away from the properties.</p> <p>A Fulton Hogan worker at the scene said roadworkers had not expected the underground&nbsp;pipe to extend as far as it did.</p> <p>Stephen Kimber, who is uninsured, feared his house would &quot;smell like a toilet&quot; once&nbsp;the water was gone.</p> <p>The resulting silt would leave his house damp, he said.</p> <p>&quot;But I know if I put the heat on to try and warm the place up, it'll start to smell like a toilet.&quot;</p> <p>Redcliffs resident Phillipa Foulds returned&nbsp;from orchestra practice at noon&nbsp;to discover water lapping near her garage and flowing through neighbouring houses.</p> <p>She said a roadworker had explained to her that the miller was &quot;absolutely brutal on anything it hits&quot;.</p> <p>Foulds was unfazed by the moat outside.</p> <p>&quot;Oh, we're used to flooding,&quot; she said.</p> <p>&quot;This is nothing.&quot;</p> <p>The majority of the water had been pumped away by 1pm.&nbsp;</p> <p>A Christchurch City Council spokeswoman said at 2pm said no one was without water.&nbsp;</p> <div> <span>&nbsp;</span> </div>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816755,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154716+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:47 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Water main broken in Redcliffs\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816755,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182735/755/11816755.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11817269,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T163215+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:32 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Dean Kozanic\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"the-press\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"The Press\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Streets and properties have been flooded in Redcliffs, Christchurch, after water main was gouged.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n           