ch\",\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": null,\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"16:44 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"intro\": null,\n                    \"images\": [\n                        {\n                            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T132559+1200\",\n                            \"datetime_display\": \"13:25 21/05/2015\",\n                            \"creditline\": \"Dean Kozanic\",\n                            \"source_code\": \"the-press\",\n                            \"source_title\": \"The Press\",\n                            \"caption\": \"Stephen Kimber and his dog Ripper won't need to water the garden for a while.\",\n                            \"variants\": [\n                                {\n                                    \"id\": 11815109,\n                                    \"layout\": \"1024 Landscape\",\n                                    \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182735/109/11815109.jpg\",\n                                    \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                                    \"width\": \"1024\",\n                                    \"height\": \"683\"\n                                }\n                            ]\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T141216+1200\",\n                            \"datetime_display\": \"14:12 21/05/2015\",\n                            \"creditline\": \"Dean Kozanic\",\n                            \"source_code\": \"the-press\",\n                            \"source_title\": \"The Press\",\n                            \"caption\": \"Streets and properties have been flooded in Redcliffs, Christchurch after water main burst.\",\n                            \"variants\": [\n                                {\n                                    \"id\": 11815577,\n                                    \"layout\": \"1024 Landscape\",\n                                    \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182735/577/11815577.jpg\",\n                                    \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                                    \"width\": \"1024\",\n                                    \"height\": \"683\"\n                                }\n                            ]\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T141217+1200\",\n                            \"datetime_display\": \"14:12 21/05/2015\",\n                            \"creditline\": \"Dean Kozanic\",\n                            \"source_code\": \"the-press\",\n                            \"source_title\": \"The Press\",\n                            \"caption\": \"Streets and properties have been flooded in Redcliffs, Christchurch after water main burst.\",\n                            \"variants\": [\n                                {\n                                    \"id\": 11815578,\n                                    \"layout\": \"1024 Landscape\",\n                                    \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182735/578/11815578.jpg\",\n                                    \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                                    \"width\": \"1024\",\n                                    \"height\": \"683\"\n                                }\n                            ]\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T141217+1200\",\n                            \"datetime_display\": \"14:12 21/05/2015\",\n                            \"creditline\": \"Dean Kozanic\",\n                            \"source_code\": \"the-press\",\n                            \"source_title\": \"The Press\",\n                            \"caption\": \"Streets and properties have been flooded in Redcliffs, Christchurch after water main burst.\",\n                            \"variants\": [\n                                {\n                                    \"id\": 11815579,\n                                    \"layout\": \"1024 Landscape\",\n                                    \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432182735/579/11815579.jpg\",\n                                    \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                                    \"width\": \"1024\",\n                                    \"height\": \"682\"\n                                }\n                            ]\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68746129,\n            \"path\": \"/life-style/food-wine/food-news/68746129/Would-you-eat-this-Carls-Jr-burger\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/life-style/food-wine/food-news/68746129/Would-you-eat-this-Carls-Jr-burger\",\n            \"section\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"section-home\": \"Food News\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Life & Style\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-image\",\n            \"title\": \"Would you eat this Carl's Jr burger?\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Would you eat this burger?\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T153102+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"15:31 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"CRAIG GIAMMONA\",\n            \"source_code\": \"smh\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Sydney Morning Herald\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/life-style/food-wine/food-news/68746129\",\n            \"intro\": \"Would you like fries in that?\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"It's got beef, hot dogs and crisps and weighs in at a whopping 1080 calories.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>Would you like fries in that?</p> <p>Forget healthy food habits.&nbsp;A US&nbsp;fast-food chain has started selling&nbsp;what is possibly the world's fattest-ever burger - a 1080-calorie&nbsp;burger that it hopes appeals to Americans' patriotic spirit, along with their appetites.</p> <p>Carl's Jr's&nbsp;<i>The Most American Thickburger&nbsp;</i>features&nbsp;a beef patty topped with hot dogs and a layer of potato crisps, combining three&nbsp;barbecue staples in a creation aimed squarely at the fast-food chain's core customers: &quot;young, hungry guys&quot;.</p> <p>It has more than double the calories of a McDonald's Big Mac.</p> <p>&quot;People love these big, juicy, indulgent burgers,&quot; said Andy Puzder, the chief executive officer of closely held CKE Restaurants, the parent company of Carl's Jr. &quot;We know who we are and we know how to appeal to our customers.&quot;</p> <p>The idea for the burger has been percolating inside the California-based company for almost five years, Puzder said. The chain toyed with including french fries on the burger, but found they wouldn't hold up against the moisture inside the sandwich. They got too soggy. The same was true of regular potato chips, so Carl's Jr settled on kettle-cooked chips that are a bit hardier.</p> <p><img src=\\\"http://static.stuff.co.nz/1432178742/504/11816504.jpg\\\" /></p> <p>The fast-food chain, which is controlled by the private-equity firm Roark Capital, has about 3500 restaurants worldwide, including locations in New Zealand.</p> <p>As part of its strategy of going after 18- to 34-year-old men, the <a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/life-style/videos/9023988/Carls-Jr-ads-Too-much\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">company's ads feature scantily clad models and actresses</a>, including Paris Hilton, Kim Kardashian and Charlotte McKinney. The new commercials for the American burger star <i>Sports Illustrated</i> swimsuit model Samantha Hoopes, who appears in a hot tub wearing an American flag bikini.</p> <p>&quot;It really emphasises the all-American nature of this burger and the taste sensation when you bite into it,&quot; Puzder said.</p> <p><b>Complaints drive sales</b></p> <p>The 64-year-old CEO said he has killed previous ads that he found too suggestive. He also shows each one to his wife before giving the green&nbsp;light. The commercials generate some complaints, but the attention - whether good or bad - ultimately helps the brand, Puzder said.</p> <p>&quot;Beautiful women eating burgers and washing cars - what could be more American than that? I'm OK with it,&quot; he said. &quot;We don't want to offend anyone, but the complaints seem to drive sales.&quot;</p> <p>Carl's Jr's best performing restaurant over the last two years is in Williston, North Dakota, where sales topped $US4 million ($5.5m) in 2014, almost four times the national average. Puzder attributed the performance to the male workers who have swarmed North Dakota looking for jobs in the oil and gas industry.</p> <p><b>Nutritional concerns</b></p> <p>And what about health concerns? With McDonald's dabbling with kale, consumers&nbsp;are probably more focused on nutrition than ever before. Do they really want a burger topped with chips and hot dogs that packs 64 grams of fat, almost three times as much as a Big Mac?</p> <p>Yes, Puzder said. Carl's Jr offers turkey burgers and has an all-natural patty made with beef raised without antibiotics, but those items don't sell as well as the more indulgent burgers.</p> <p>&quot;I'm not the food police,&quot; Puzder said. &quot;My job isn't to dictate to people what to eat. My job is to figure out what people want and sell it to them.&quot;</p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816770,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154737+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:47 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Fab Fernandez, CKE Restaurants\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The burger chain's ad stars Sports Illustrated swimsuit model Samantha Hoopes.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816770,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180057/770/11816770.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"59\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816771,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154738+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:47 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Fab Fernandez, CKE Restaurants\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The burger chain's ad stars Sports Illustrated swimsuit model Samantha Hoopes.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816771,\n                            \"layout\": \"Standard Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180058/771/11816771.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"620\",\n                            \"height\": \"348\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816772,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T154738+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:47 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Fab Fernandez, CKE Restaurants\",\n                    \"caption\": \"The burger chain's ad stars Sports Illustrated swimsuit model Samantha Hoopes.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816772,\n                            \"layout\": \"Strap Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180058/772/11816772.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"300