"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816835,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T155137+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:51 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Ross Giblin\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Finance Minister Bill English at the printing of the 2015 Budget at Printlink, Petone.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816835,\n                            \"layout\": \"Defcon Image\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432180297/835/11816835.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"417\",\n                            \"height\": \"220\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                }\n            ],\n            \"videos\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816395,\n                    \"layout\": \"Standard Video\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"aap\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"AAP\",\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T151532+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:15 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Parliament TV\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Finance Minister Bill English delivers the Budget 2015 announcing an changes to Kiwi Saver, benefits and border security.\",\n                    \"src\": \"http://file2.stuff.co.nz/1432178132/396/11816396.mp4\",\n                    \"video_poster\": {\n                        \"id\": 11816397,\n                        \"layout\": \"Video Image\",\n                        \"src\": \"http://file2.stuff.co.nz/1432180634/397/11816397.jpg\",\n                        \"width\": \"640\",\n                        \"height\": \"360\"\n                    }\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 68729413,\n            \"path\": \"/business/68729413/Budget-2015-Tackling-hardship-with-an-eye-to-future-tax-cuts\",\n            \"url\": \"http://www.stuff.co.nz/_json/business/68729413/Budget-2015-Tackling-hardship-with-an-eye-to-future-tax-cuts\",\n            \"section\": \"Politics\",\n            \"section-home\": \"Business\",\n            \"section-top-level\": \"Business\",\n            \"layout\": \"landscape-video\",\n            \"title\": \"Budget 2015: Tackling hardship with an eye to future tax cuts\",\n            \"subhead\": null,\n            \"alt_headline\": \"Family benefit to rise\",\n            \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150440+1200\",\n            \"datetime_display\": \"15:04 21/05/2015\",\n            \"byline\": \"HAMISH RUTHERFORD\",\n            \"source_code\": \"1national-newsroom\",\n            \"source_name\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"category_id\": \"Stuff\",\n            \"stream_id\": \"stuff/business/68729413\",\n            \"intro\": \"Beneficiaries will see the largest boost to their incomes in more than 40 years in 2016, as Finance Minister Bill English delivers a Budget targeted firmly at poorer Kiwi children.\",\n            \"alt_intro\": \"Beneficiaries will see the largest boost to their incomes in more than 40 years in 2016, as Finance Minister Bill English delivers a Budget targeted firmly at poorer Kiwi children.\",\n            \"body\": \"<p>Beneficiaries will see the largest boost to their incomes in more than 40 years in 2016, as Finance Minister Bill English delivers a Budget targeted firmly at poorer Kiwi children.</p> <p><b>READ MORE:</b></p> <p><b>*&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/68736405/budget-live-stream.html\\\">LIVE: Watch the Budget speech and debate in Parliament<br /> </a>* <a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/68741678/budget-2015-modest-tax-cuts-flagged-for-2017\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Modest tax cuts for 2017<br /> *&nbsp;</a><a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/68742199/budget-2015-benefits-rise-in-bid-to-tackle-child-poverty\\\">Benefits to rise, but there's a catch</a>&nbsp;<br /> *&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/68741678/budget-2015-modest-tax-cuts-flagged-for-2017\\\">Modest tax cuts for 2017<br /> </a>* <a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/life-style/home-property/68725628/government-to-devote-430-hectares-to-help-solve-auckland-housing-crisis\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Government to devote 430 hectares to help solve Auckland housing crisis<br /> </a>* <a href=\\\"http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/68726384/beehive-live-new-zealand-budget-2015\\\">Beehive Live: New Zealand Budget 2015</a></b></p> <p>In a surprise move, English's seventh Budget tackles hardship among the poorest households. There is a package including $790 million over four years to boost welfare payments for beneficiaries with children and low income parents receiving Working for Families payments.</p> <p>There is a sting in the tail of the increases for beneficiaries though, as well as a new tax on travel and the abolition of a popular subsidy on saving.</p> <p>The Budget, and its focus on lower incomes, appears aimed squarly at clearing the path for future tax cuts.</p> <p>A cut in income taxes is slated as a fiscal priority for the first time, starting in 2017, likely to coincide with the next election.</p> <p>Families on benefits with children will get another $25 a week - $1300 a year. It will be the first time since 1972 that payments have been increased by more than inflation.</p> <p>Working for Families payments will also be increased for low and middle income families by up to $12.50 a week, although households earning $88,000 or above will see a small cut. The changes come into effect on April 1, 2016.</p> <p>In a statement, Prime Minister John Key said that providing support for children in hardship was a priority. The increases announced in the Budget &quot;will make a real difference by allowing parents to better provide for their children&quot;, Key said.</p> <p>English said the increases were balanced to not undermine the incentive to work while &quot;address[ing] our concern about children whose family's resources have been falling behind other households&quot;.</p> <p>Sole parents will now have to be &quot;work ready&quot; when their youngest child turns three (down from five years old), and the hours they are expected to work rises from 15 to 20 hours.</p> <p>Potential savers will foot much of the cost of the package. By the time you read this, the $1000 &quot;kickstart&quot; to join KiwiSaver has already been abolished.</p> <p>Travellers will also be stung with a new international departure levy to help cover the costs of new biosecurity measures.</p> <p>Although the exact structure of the levy is yet to be determined, it is expected raise $100m a year, adding $16 to the cost of flying to New Zealand and $6 to departing.</p> <p>Key, the Minister of Tourism, has previously lobbied against similar - albeit larger - taxes in countries such as the United Kingdom.</p> <p>Thursday's Budget revealed, once again, that the Government has abandoned attempts to reach surplus this year, with Treasury forecasting a deficit of $684m. Next year's predicted surplus is a wafer thin $176m.</p> <p>Since the forecasts were prepared, dairy prices have continued to slide.</p> <p><b>KEY POINTS</b></p> <p>-$790 million over four years for increased welfare payments and higher Working for Families payments in return for greater work obligations</p> <p>-No surplus, and next year's forecast surplus is within the margin of error</p> <p>-An immediate end to the $1000 Kiwisaver kickstart payment</p> <p>-A new $100 million tax on international travel to cover the cost of border protection and customs activities.</p>\",\n            \"images\": [\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816260,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150529+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:05 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": null,\n                    \"caption\": \"Finance minister Bill English announcing his 'Hardship' budget.\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816260,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432177529/260/11816260.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816261,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150529+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:05 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Ross Giblin\",\n                    \"source_code\": \"fairfax-media\",\n                    \"source_name\": \"Fairfax Media\",\n                    \"caption\": \"Budget defcon 2015\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                        {\n                            \"id\": 11816261,\n                            \"layout\": \"Small Thumbnail\",\n                            \"src\": \"http://static2.stuff.co.nz/1432177529/261/11816261.jpg\",\n                            \"media_type\": \"Photo\",\n                            \"width\": \"90\",\n                            \"height\": \"60\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"id\": 11816262,\n                    \"datetime_iso8601\": \"20150521T150529+1200\",\n                    \"datetime_display\": \"15:05 21/05/2015\",\n                    \"creditline\": \"Ross Giblin\",\n        